<recipe>
	<name>Tahoe Banana-Oat Pancakes</name>
	<yield_count>4</yield_count>
	<yield_measure>Servings</yield_measure>
	<notes>My friend Kristi had access to a cabin in Tahoe and used to invite us all up for a weekend of skiing and frivolity.   Knowing that I was going to be on the hook for at least one meal, I delved for the first time into  Epicurious and dug up these hearty fellers.  I recall searching high and low for wheat germ that first time at the unfamiliar Stateline Raley's megamarket. Double whammy: where'd you'd find it, and where'd you find it -here-.

Raleys is like that.</notes>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>old-fashioned oats</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>nonfat milk</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>mashed ripe bananas (about 3 med)</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>eggs</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2 Tbl</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>wheat germ</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>ground cinnamon</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 1/2 cups</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>oat-bran/mixed grain pancake mix</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<preparation>Mix oats and milk in a large bowl.  Let stand until oats are soft (about 15 minutes).  Mix in mashed bananas, eggs, wheat germ and cinnamon. Gradually stir in pancake mix (batter will be very thick).</preparation>
